&lt;p&gt;The big question is &amp;ldquo;Why does extended validation cost so much more?&amp;rdquo; and it is simply gatekeeping at its best. Many SSL companies will tell you it is because the &amp;ldquo;vetting process is harder&amp;rdquo;, but I smell bullshit on that. It costs usually double and sometimes more. The only difference is it requires a hardware cryptographic key and Microsoft smartscreen immediately gives it a pass on all scans.&lt;/p&gt;



